00:01:05.480 --> 00:01:07.730 align:middle line:90%
Oh my god.

00:01:07.730 --> 00:01:11.022 align:middle line:84%
So what is this
enlightened living?

00:01:11.022 --> 00:01:12.980 align:middle line:10%
>> SINGH: You know,
everyone's wanting to go up

00:01:12.980 --> 00:01:16.320 align:middle line:10%
into the ethers or have
enlightenment handed to them

00:01:16.320 --> 00:01:17.969 align:middle line:10%
by someone else
outside of themselves.

00:01:17.969 --> 00:01:19.760 align:middle line:10%
And what I have discovered
through my life,

00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:21.718 align:middle line:10%
and I'm sure you have
discovered through diving

00:01:21.718 --> 00:01:23.650 align:middle line:10%
into your passions
and your heart,

00:01:23.650 --> 00:01:25.610 align:middle line:10%
is that enlightenment
is something

00:01:25.610 --> 00:01:27.520 align:middle line:10%
that is a self-induced process.

00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:29.290 align:middle line:10%
It's a self-illumination
process.

00:01:29.290 --> 00:01:32.590 align:middle line:10%
It is something that we have to
invite and invoke and embody.

00:01:32.590 --> 00:01:34.580 align:middle line:10%
Because we're meant
to be on planet Earth.

00:01:34.580 --> 00:01:36.790 align:middle line:10%
We're not meant to be
floating in the stars.

00:01:36.790 --> 00:01:38.890 align:middle line:10%
That is part of
who we are, but we

00:01:38.890 --> 00:01:42.490 align:middle line:10%
are meant to be here
grounded in the essence

00:01:42.490 --> 00:01:44.990 align:middle line:10%
that we are, creating from
that creative essence.

00:01:44.990 --> 00:01:47.500 align:middle line:10%
Because we are the sons
and daughters of the divine

00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:49.340 align:middle line:10%
here to express
creative capacity.

00:01:49.340 --> 00:01:50.032 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:01:50.032 --> 00:01:53.160 align:middle line:10%
So how would you summarize
this enlightenment?

00:01:53.160 --> 00:01:55.520 align:middle line:10%
So we're all entitled
to it, right?

00:01:55.520 --> 00:01:56.400 align:middle line:10%
>> SINGH: Yes.

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:58.775 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: And then what does
it look like on a day-to-day

00:01:58.775 --> 00:01:59.660 align:middle line:10%
basis?

00:01:59.660 --> 00:02:02.670 align:middle line:10%
>> SINGH: Enlightenment to me
is our ability to understand,

00:02:02.670 --> 00:02:04.600 align:middle line:10%
first and foremost,
that we're all masters.

00:02:04.600 --> 00:02:07.650 align:middle line:10%
Every single one of us
is a master walking.

00:02:07.650 --> 00:02:09.949 align:middle line:10%
The misrepresentation
about mastery

00:02:09.949 --> 00:02:12.480 align:middle line:10%
is that a master is someone
with miracles all around them

00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:13.751 align:middle line:10%
all the time.

00:02:13.751 --> 00:02:14.750 align:middle line:10%
But that's not a master.

00:02:14.750 --> 00:02:15.990 align:middle line:10%
That would be too easy.

00:02:15.990 --> 00:02:18.890 align:middle line:10%
A master is someone that has
the obstacles in their life

00:02:18.890 --> 00:02:21.160 align:middle line:10%
but understands how to
navigate through them

00:02:21.160 --> 00:02:23.930 align:middle line:10%
and creates despite those
obstacles in their life.

00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:25.640 align:middle line:10%
That is true mastery.

00:02:25.640 --> 00:02:28.270 align:middle line:10%
And when we step into
that and we understand

00:02:28.270 --> 00:02:29.870 align:middle line:10%
that when we dive
into our shadows

00:02:29.870 --> 00:02:33.060 align:middle line:10%
and we dive into the difficulty
that shows up in life

00:02:33.060 --> 00:02:36.500 align:middle line:10%
and we merge the fear and the
love, the dark and the light

00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:39.830 align:middle line:10%
and that we allow it to be
in the now fully present with

00:02:39.830 --> 00:02:42.960 align:middle line:10%
emotion, that's where we
tap into enlightenment,

00:02:42.960 --> 00:02:46.650 align:middle line:10%
because we're understanding
that we're not just human.

00:02:46.650 --> 00:02:48.610 align:middle line:10%
This is a physical space suit.

00:02:48.610 --> 00:02:51.890 align:middle line:10%
We're not even spiritual beings
having a human experience.

00:02:51.890 --> 00:02:53.100 align:middle line:10%
I don't believe that.

00:02:53.100 --> 00:02:54.850 align:middle line:10%
Because if we were
spiritual beings having

00:02:54.850 --> 00:02:56.790 align:middle line:10%
a human experience,
then when we die,

00:02:56.790 --> 00:02:59.060 align:middle line:10%
we're just as separate
as we are now.

00:02:59.060 --> 00:03:00.950 align:middle line:10%
So there must be
something beyond that.

00:03:00.950 --> 00:03:04.460 align:middle line:10%
I believe we are experience
experiencing itself.

00:03:04.460 --> 00:03:07.540 align:middle line:10%
And enlightenment is
fully embodying and living

00:03:07.540 --> 00:03:10.980 align:middle line:10%
as experience in each and
every moment of every day.

00:03:10.980 --> 00:03:15.370 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: I love when you say
in the TED talk or even just

00:03:15.370 --> 00:03:17.857 align:middle line:10%
the title of your first
book, "Conversations with

00:03:17.857 --> 00:03:20.190 align:middle line:10%
the Universe," that we're
always, actually we're always,

00:03:20.190 --> 00:03:22.240 align:middle line:10%
always having a conversation
with the universe.

00:03:22.240 --> 00:03:23.290 align:middle line:90%
Tell us more.

00:03:23.290 --> 00:03:24.290 align:middle line:90%
So there are signs, huh?

00:03:24.290 --> 00:03:26.222 align:middle line:84%
There's things
that happen to us.

00:03:26.222 --> 00:03:27.680 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot that
happened to you.

00:03:27.680 --> 00:03:29.388 align:middle line:84%
I want to get into
your story after that,

00:03:29.388 --> 00:03:31.450 align:middle line:84%
because my goodness
did you ever go

00:03:31.450 --> 00:03:32.974 align:middle line:84%
through the dark
night of the soul.

00:03:32.974 --> 00:03:35.390 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: Well, I think that
that's why I wrote this book.

00:03:35.390 --> 00:03:37.150 align:middle line:84%
And the reason for
writing "Conversations

00:03:37.150 --> 00:03:40.079 align:middle line:84%
with the Universe" is because
I realized I didn't trust life.

00:03:40.079 --> 00:03:41.245 align:middle line:90%
I didn't trust the universe.

00:03:41.245 --> 00:03:42.910 align:middle line:90%
I didn't trust God.

00:03:42.910 --> 00:03:44.220 align:middle line:90%
I didn't trust other people.

00:03:44.220 --> 00:03:46.240 align:middle line:84%
Most of all, I
didn't trust myself.

00:03:46.240 --> 00:03:47.870 align:middle line:84%
And so I had to
build that trust.

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:49.975 align:middle line:84%
And how that came
in is discovering

00:03:49.975 --> 00:03:52.100 align:middle line:84%
that there were signs,
symbols, and synchronicities

00:03:52.100 --> 00:03:55.460 align:middle line:84%
showing up, but not just passing
them by when they showed up,

00:03:55.460 --> 00:03:57.210 align:middle line:90%
starting to really look at them.

00:03:57.210 --> 00:03:59.930 align:middle line:84%
And the truth is each
and every one of us

00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:02.780 align:middle line:84%
gets signs all of the
time, all day long.

00:04:02.780 --> 00:04:06.670 align:middle line:84%
We are each just as special
as the other and not so.

00:04:06.670 --> 00:04:08.800 align:middle line:10%
And we have to understand
that if we just simply

00:04:08.800 --> 00:04:10.350 align:middle line:10%
look at what's going
on in our lives

00:04:10.350 --> 00:04:12.650 align:middle line:10%
from the people to the
pets to the children

00:04:12.650 --> 00:04:15.790 align:middle line:10%
to the experiences, the
obstacles, and the challenges,

00:04:15.790 --> 00:04:18.660 align:middle line:10%
they're all just
messages showing us

00:04:18.660 --> 00:04:21.890 align:middle line:10%
who we are so that we can
grow and move beyond them.

00:04:21.890 --> 00:04:23.950 align:middle line:10%
And that's how I began
the journey of discovering

00:04:23.950 --> 00:04:26.062 align:middle line:10%
the messages show up everywhere.

00:04:26.062 --> 00:04:28.270 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: How can we not
interpret when something bad

00:04:28.270 --> 00:04:31.810 align:middle line:10%
happens to us, like a big
challenge, how can we not say,

00:04:31.810 --> 00:04:35.100 align:middle line:10%
I'm not good enough, I'm not
worth it, here we are again,

00:04:35.100 --> 00:04:37.610 align:middle line:10%
this is not for me, this
is for those two ladies,

00:04:37.610 --> 00:04:39.080 align:middle line:10%
this is not me here?

00:04:39.080 --> 00:04:39.990 align:middle line:10%
>> SINGH: Yeah.

00:04:39.990 --> 00:04:41.610 align:middle line:10%
We're asking the
wrong questions.

00:04:41.610 --> 00:04:44.490 align:middle line:10%
Because usually when something
bad happens, Lilou, people go,

00:04:44.490 --> 00:04:46.610 align:middle line:10%
why is this happening to me?

00:04:46.610 --> 00:04:48.770 align:middle line:10%
Why did this take
place in my life?

00:04:48.770 --> 00:04:49.920 align:middle line:10%
What did I do wrong?

00:04:49.920 --> 00:04:52.980 align:middle line:10%
Instead of, where is that in me?

00:04:52.980 --> 00:04:55.300 align:middle line:10%
Because if we say, where
is that challenge in me

00:04:55.300 --> 00:04:57.540 align:middle line:10%
or where is that
terrorism in me or where

00:04:57.540 --> 00:05:00.950 align:middle line:10%
is that idol that I like
in me, then all of a sudden

00:05:00.950 --> 00:05:04.440 align:middle line:10%
we become at one with it
rather than that's that thing

00:05:04.440 --> 00:05:08.640 align:middle line:10%
I didn't want to happen and I'm
over here trying to avoid it.

00:05:08.640 --> 00:05:10.310 align:middle line:90%
Instead, we merge with it.

00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:13.050 align:middle line:84%
And when we merge with it,
we discover our commonality,

00:05:13.050 --> 00:05:15.710 align:middle line:84%
and then we find the gift
that's actually inside of it.

00:05:15.710 --> 00:05:17.590 align:middle line:84%
And it will be a
message and a gift.

00:05:17.590 --> 00:05:18.470 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:05:18.470 --> 00:05:23.290 align:middle line:84%
It's hard when we see anger
in another one or criticism

00:05:23.290 --> 00:05:26.020 align:middle line:90%
and to be with that negativity.

00:05:26.020 --> 00:05:29.352 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes a lot of us prefer
to escape or rage back.

00:05:29.352 --> 00:05:31.810 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: Well, then we're
going to stay in our victimhood.

00:05:31.810 --> 00:05:33.518 align:middle line:84%
Because the easiest
thing to do right now

00:05:33.518 --> 00:05:35.640 align:middle line:84%
is to project onto
another person.

00:05:35.640 --> 00:05:39.160 align:middle line:84%
But if we can truly look at
everything as simply a message,

00:05:39.160 --> 00:05:42.040 align:middle line:84%
then we're going to discover
that it's all actually us.

00:05:42.040 --> 00:05:44.390 align:middle line:84%
I tell people you're
not on a journey.

00:05:44.390 --> 00:05:46.080 align:middle line:90%
You are the journey.

00:05:46.080 --> 00:05:47.630 align:middle line:90%
You're not in the world.

00:05:47.630 --> 00:05:50.950 align:middle line:10%
You are every piece and part
of the world showing up.

00:05:50.950 --> 00:05:53.150 align:middle line:10%
You are experience
experiencing itself,

00:05:53.150 --> 00:05:57.500 align:middle line:10%
and everything outside of
you is you showing you you.

00:05:57.500 --> 00:05:59.560 align:middle line:10%
There really is
nothing out there.

00:05:59.560 --> 00:06:02.620 align:middle line:10%
As real as it feels and it
looks, there's nothing there.

00:06:02.620 --> 00:06:03.890 align:middle line:10%
There's only you.

00:06:03.890 --> 00:06:06.230 align:middle line:10%
And you've created
this dynamic play

00:06:06.230 --> 00:06:10.180 align:middle line:10%
to show you your full capacity,
from its dark to its light.

00:06:10.180 --> 00:06:13.485 align:middle line:10%
So when you embrace that,
that's enlightenment.

00:06:13.485 --> 00:06:16.050 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: Do you think we all
need to go through the dark

00:06:16.050 --> 00:06:20.000 align:middle line:10%
night of the soul like you did
or the suffering to feel this

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.910 align:middle line:10%
enlightenment or to be
that connected to life?

00:06:24.910 --> 00:06:27.500 align:middle line:10%
>> SINGH: I don't think we
have to, but I think we choose

00:06:27.500 --> 00:06:29.510 align:middle line:10%
to because we love a good story.

00:06:29.510 --> 00:06:30.500 align:middle line:10%
We're each a sacred--

00:06:30.500 --> 00:06:31.709 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: You got a good one.

00:06:31.709 --> 00:06:33.124 align:middle line:10%
>> SINGH: I got a
really good one.

00:06:33.124 --> 00:06:34.680 align:middle line:10%
We are each a
sacred text walking.

00:06:34.680 --> 00:06:36.920 align:middle line:10%
We are no different
than any other holy book

00:06:36.920 --> 00:06:38.300 align:middle line:10%
that has been written.

00:06:38.300 --> 00:06:42.060 align:middle line:10%
We are a sacred text, in that we
each possess pearls of wisdom.

00:06:42.060 --> 00:06:44.370 align:middle line:10%
We also each possess story.

00:06:44.370 --> 00:06:46.460 align:middle line:10%
And there's some stuff
that's been made up,

00:06:46.460 --> 00:06:48.840 align:middle line:10%
because we're good at
making up some stuff,

00:06:48.840 --> 00:06:50.910 align:middle line:10%
and that's what creates
the sacred story

00:06:50.910 --> 00:06:52.600 align:middle line:10%
of the hero or the heroine.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:54.380 align:middle line:10%
And that's what we
really came here for.

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:57.180 align:middle line:10%
We want to see
ourselves as ugly so

00:06:57.180 --> 00:06:58.830 align:middle line:10%
that we can discover our beauty.

00:06:58.830 --> 00:07:01.610 align:middle line:10%
We want to feel weak so
that we know our power.

00:07:01.610 --> 00:07:04.680 align:middle line:10%
We can't know something
unless we know the opposite.

00:07:04.680 --> 00:07:07.340 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: So we're talking
here of also being vulnerable

00:07:07.340 --> 00:07:10.320 align:middle line:10%
to what's so, what's happening,
even when we have those dark

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:13.810 align:middle line:10%
moments or the anger comes
up, being OK with that.

00:07:13.810 --> 00:07:15.534 align:middle line:90%
Is that part of the practices?

00:07:15.534 --> 00:07:17.950 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: I think that's the
step into the golden age that

00:07:17.950 --> 00:07:19.720 align:middle line:90%
has not been taken before.

00:07:19.720 --> 00:07:20.890 align:middle line:90%
We've been wearing masks.

00:07:20.890 --> 00:07:22.560 align:middle line:84%
We've been trying to
run from our pain.

00:07:22.560 --> 00:07:25.800 align:middle line:84%
We've been trying to run
from the truth of all

00:07:25.800 --> 00:07:27.720 align:middle line:84%
the negativity
that we've created

00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:29.740 align:middle line:84%
or the lowness that we
have found ourselves in

00:07:29.740 --> 00:07:31.957 align:middle line:84%
and trying to cover that
up with other things.

00:07:31.957 --> 00:07:33.540 align:middle line:84%
We've been trying
to fill ourselves up

00:07:33.540 --> 00:07:36.940 align:middle line:84%
with everything outside of us
rather than diving into us.

00:07:36.940 --> 00:07:39.320 align:middle line:10%
And if instead we
allow ourselves

00:07:39.320 --> 00:07:42.290 align:middle line:10%
to understand that it's all
beautiful, that it's all here

00:07:42.290 --> 00:07:45.750 align:middle line:10%
for the taking and the
celebration, that actually is

00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:49.450 align:middle line:10%
those dark moments in
life that create us,

00:07:49.450 --> 00:07:52.700 align:middle line:10%
that's where the ember, the
fire of the light starts,

00:07:52.700 --> 00:07:55.350 align:middle line:10%
and that is where the contract
has been made so that we can

00:07:55.350 --> 00:07:57.480 align:middle line:10%
create that beautiful
sacred story

00:07:57.480 --> 00:07:59.200 align:middle line:10%
and then discover
that we are actually

00:07:59.200 --> 00:08:00.660 align:middle line:10%
the divine presence walking.

00:08:00.660 --> 00:08:02.120 align:middle line:10%
Each and every one
of us is a piece

00:08:02.120 --> 00:08:06.320 align:middle line:10%
of the divine that holds a
unique genius that is here

00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:08.550 align:middle line:10%
to be expressed and experienced.

00:08:08.550 --> 00:08:12.540 align:middle line:10%
And when we have the courage
to dive into that unique genius

00:08:12.540 --> 00:08:14.990 align:middle line:10%
and share it with the world,
like you do with all the work

00:08:14.990 --> 00:08:15.910 align:middle line:10%
that you do--

00:08:15.910 --> 00:08:16.350 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: Thank you.

00:08:16.350 --> 00:08:17.990 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: --then we
ripple out in the world,

00:08:17.990 --> 00:08:19.290 align:middle line:90%
and it affects other people.

00:08:19.290 --> 00:08:21.110 align:middle line:84%
But we have to do
it for us first,

00:08:21.110 --> 00:08:22.570 align:middle line:90%
because we're the only one here.

00:08:22.570 --> 00:08:24.747 align:middle line:90%
And only then can it ripple out.

00:08:24.747 --> 00:08:26.330 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: How do you
call that moment,

00:08:26.330 --> 00:08:29.377 align:middle line:10%
that turning point or
that tipping point moment?

00:08:29.377 --> 00:08:30.710 align:middle line:10%
Is there such a thing, actually?

00:08:30.710 --> 00:08:32.409 align:middle line:10%
Is it very--

00:08:32.409 --> 00:08:35.360 align:middle line:10%
>> SINGH: A lot of writers talk
about things being a tipping

00:08:35.360 --> 00:08:36.870 align:middle line:10%
point or a turning point.

00:08:36.870 --> 00:08:39.530 align:middle line:84%
To me, that's still
putting it on the outside.

00:08:39.530 --> 00:08:42.190 align:middle line:84%
I see it as a churning
point, and that

00:08:42.190 --> 00:08:43.450 align:middle line:90%
takes place on the inside.

00:08:43.450 --> 00:08:45.050 align:middle line:84%
Just like milk
can become butter,

00:08:45.050 --> 00:08:47.600 align:middle line:84%
it happens because of the
agitation and the churning that

00:08:47.600 --> 00:08:50.480 align:middle line:84%
takes place, everything
that supposedly is going on

00:08:50.480 --> 00:08:54.780 align:middle line:84%
in our world or in our lives is
actually that agitation place

00:08:54.780 --> 00:08:58.180 align:middle line:84%
so that we start to realize
I feel tight in my skin,

00:08:58.180 --> 00:08:59.640 align:middle line:90%
I do feel uncomfortable.

00:08:59.640 --> 00:09:02.085 align:middle line:84%
There's something inside
of me that's constricting,

00:09:02.085 --> 00:09:03.820 align:middle line:84%
and it's not trying
to make me smaller.

00:09:03.820 --> 00:09:06.860 align:middle line:84%
It trying to get me to realize
that there's something bigger

00:09:06.860 --> 00:09:10.220 align:middle line:84%
inside of me that will no
longer fit in the identity, ego,

00:09:10.220 --> 00:09:12.140 align:middle line:84%
and personality
that I've built up.

00:09:12.140 --> 00:09:14.420 align:middle line:84%
You can't keep
spirit in a bottle.

00:09:14.420 --> 00:09:15.750 align:middle line:90%
And that's what we each are.

00:09:15.750 --> 00:09:18.780 align:middle line:84%
And when we step into the full
essence of the spiritual play

00:09:18.780 --> 00:09:21.260 align:middle line:84%
that we are, then
all of a sudden

00:09:21.260 --> 00:09:24.486 align:middle line:84%
we dive into the unknown self
rather than the known self.

00:09:24.486 --> 00:09:25.860 align:middle line:84%
And that makes
all the difference

00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:27.480 align:middle line:84%
in the world in
terms of our bliss

00:09:27.480 --> 00:09:29.490 align:middle line:90%
and our joy and our happiness.

00:09:29.490 --> 00:09:32.410 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: When you say unknown,
that's really the journey that

00:09:32.410 --> 00:09:37.340 align:middle line:84%
you're on now, not really
knowing and opening up yourself

00:09:37.340 --> 00:09:38.547 align:middle line:90%
to this guidance?

00:09:38.547 --> 00:09:39.130 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Yes.

00:09:39.130 --> 00:09:42.170 align:middle line:84%
When I left my 18-year
arranged marriage a year

00:09:42.170 --> 00:09:45.150 align:middle line:84%
and a half ago, I
realized who I was

00:09:45.150 --> 00:09:47.360 align:middle line:84%
had taken me as
far as I could go.

00:09:47.360 --> 00:09:50.180 align:middle line:84%
I was almost in the same
place I was seven years ago,

00:09:50.180 --> 00:09:53.180 align:middle line:84%
except seven years ago I was
on my prayer room floor broken,

00:09:53.180 --> 00:09:55.610 align:middle line:84%
wounded, crying, and
shattered, having gone

00:09:55.610 --> 00:09:57.840 align:middle line:84%
through tremendous
pain, betrayal,

00:09:57.840 --> 00:10:01.330 align:middle line:84%
and trying to make people love
me that just didn't want to.

00:10:01.330 --> 00:10:04.460 align:middle line:84%
And so at this point in my
life, I realized I've grown.

00:10:04.460 --> 00:10:05.000 align:middle line:90%
I've healed.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:08.000 align:middle line:84%
I've created "11:11 Magazine"
and "11:11 Talk Radio,"

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:10.230 align:middle line:84%
I share gifts with
the world, and I'm

00:10:10.230 --> 00:10:12.470 align:middle line:90%
very content and peaceful.

00:10:12.470 --> 00:10:14.570 align:middle line:90%
But I write about the bliss.

00:10:14.570 --> 00:10:16.240 align:middle line:84%
I write about if you
do what you love,

00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:17.960 align:middle line:84%
the bliss follows,
the abundance follows,

00:10:17.960 --> 00:10:20.720 align:middle line:84%
everything in your world is
the way it's supposed to be.

00:10:20.720 --> 00:10:22.082 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, where is that?

00:10:22.082 --> 00:10:23.290 align:middle line:90%
That hasn't shown up.

00:10:23.290 --> 00:10:24.010 align:middle line:90%
I'm happy.

00:10:24.010 --> 00:10:24.830 align:middle line:90%
I'm content.

00:10:24.830 --> 00:10:26.720 align:middle line:84%
I could continue
my life this way.

00:10:26.720 --> 00:10:28.260 align:middle line:90%
But where's that bliss?

00:10:28.260 --> 00:10:30.310 align:middle line:90%
I need to know where that is.

00:10:30.310 --> 00:10:32.720 align:middle line:84%
And so my known self would
never figure that out.

00:10:32.720 --> 00:10:34.740 align:middle line:90%
I had to dive into the unknown.

00:10:34.740 --> 00:10:37.960 align:middle line:84%
But the problem is people think
the unknown is the scary place

00:10:37.960 --> 00:10:39.440 align:middle line:90%
that the boogieman lives.

00:10:39.440 --> 00:10:42.470 align:middle line:84%
They think something bad's
going to happen in that unknown.

00:10:42.470 --> 00:10:44.730 align:middle line:84%
What they don't
realize is the unknown

00:10:44.730 --> 00:10:48.120 align:middle line:84%
is our greater divine self that
rests outside of here, that

00:10:48.120 --> 00:10:50.165 align:middle line:84%
actually conspires
on our behalf.

00:10:50.165 --> 00:10:54.730 align:middle line:84%
It is all of life conspiring to
give us exactly what we want,

00:10:54.730 --> 00:10:57.087 align:middle line:84%
but we have to dive
into that unknown

00:10:57.087 --> 00:10:58.295 align:middle line:90%
to discover it for ourselves.

00:10:58.295 --> 00:10:59.010 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:10:59.010 --> 00:10:59.520 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Yeah.

00:10:59.520 --> 00:11:01.880 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: We've been building
our life around security, huh?

00:11:01.880 --> 00:11:02.630 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Exactly.

00:11:02.630 --> 00:11:03.910 align:middle line:90%
And it's hard to leave that.

00:11:03.910 --> 00:11:06.500 align:middle line:84%
I left a marriage where there
was nothing but security.

00:11:06.500 --> 00:11:08.410 align:middle line:90%
I walked away from everything.

00:11:08.410 --> 00:11:10.200 align:middle line:84%
And the reason that
the Rebel Road Tour

00:11:10.200 --> 00:11:13.700 align:middle line:84%
that I'm on right now, which is
a one-woman show that I put on

00:11:13.700 --> 00:11:16.000 align:middle line:84%
that I don't plan, that
nothing was planned,

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:18.190 align:middle line:84%
nothing was controlled,
and I spontaneously show up

00:11:18.190 --> 00:11:21.870 align:middle line:84%
and I sing, do humor, and speak,
things I've never done before

00:11:21.870 --> 00:11:24.330 align:middle line:84%
because I've locked myself
in my home for 44 years

00:11:24.330 --> 00:11:27.990 align:middle line:84%
as a shy hermit, the
reason that's so powerful

00:11:27.990 --> 00:11:31.160 align:middle line:84%
is because I found
the fountain of youth.

00:11:31.160 --> 00:11:32.217 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Well, tell us.

00:11:32.217 --> 00:11:34.550 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: I actually look
younger today than I have ever

00:11:34.550 --> 00:11:36.180 align:middle line:90%
looked in my entire life.

00:11:36.180 --> 00:11:39.160 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's because I've
allowed myself to dive fully

00:11:39.160 --> 00:11:43.130 align:middle line:84%
into a passion and
very OK understanding

00:11:43.130 --> 00:11:45.270 align:middle line:84%
that I have no clue
what I'm doing.

00:11:45.270 --> 00:11:48.060 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sitting here as a
teacher or a guru for anyone.

00:11:48.060 --> 00:11:49.990 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to be
a teacher or a guru.

00:11:49.990 --> 00:11:52.690 align:middle line:84%
What I am sitting
here is as an example,

00:11:52.690 --> 00:11:54.770 align:middle line:84%
and that's what the
world needs now,

00:11:54.770 --> 00:11:57.570 align:middle line:84%
people willing to be
examples of courage that

00:11:57.570 --> 00:12:00.380 align:middle line:84%
are willing to step out there
and be who they've never been

00:12:00.380 --> 00:12:03.780 align:middle line:84%
so that they inspire themselves,
so that they enlighten

00:12:03.780 --> 00:12:05.900 align:middle line:84%
themselves, so
that they discover

00:12:05.900 --> 00:12:09.579 align:middle line:84%
what that little child within
them always wanted to do.

00:12:09.579 --> 00:12:11.120 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people come
up to me and I'm

00:12:11.120 --> 00:12:14.730 align:middle line:84%
sure come up to you, Lilou,
and say, you have such courage.

00:12:14.730 --> 00:12:17.200 align:middle line:84%
You have such courage
with what you do.

00:12:17.200 --> 00:12:18.760 align:middle line:84%
But what they
don't understand is

00:12:18.760 --> 00:12:20.920 align:middle line:84%
courage is not the
opposite of fear.

00:12:20.920 --> 00:12:23.740 align:middle line:84%
Courage is the
opposite of conformity.

00:12:23.740 --> 00:12:26.790 align:middle line:84%
Too many people have conformed
to their lives, conformed

00:12:26.790 --> 00:12:29.540 align:middle line:84%
to the restrictions that life
places on them or society

00:12:29.540 --> 00:12:31.810 align:middle line:84%
tells them they have
to live as, and that's

00:12:31.810 --> 00:12:33.180 align:middle line:90%
why they're not happy.

00:12:33.180 --> 00:12:34.710 align:middle line:84%
They've settled,
and they're living

00:12:34.710 --> 00:12:37.540 align:middle line:84%
with all the different excuses
that we make up in life that we

00:12:37.540 --> 00:12:39.987 align:middle line:84%
don't even realize are the
excuses that keep us back.

00:12:39.987 --> 00:12:42.570 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: What was keeping you
back back then in your marriage

00:12:42.570 --> 00:12:44.430 align:middle line:90%
and in your life?

00:12:44.430 --> 00:12:46.850 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: I had some of the
excuses that most people have,

00:12:46.850 --> 00:12:50.210 align:middle line:84%
things like I can't do that,
I'm a single mom with two kids.

00:12:50.210 --> 00:12:52.830 align:middle line:84%
I can't do that, my
family won't understand.

00:12:52.830 --> 00:12:54.530 align:middle line:84%
Now that I've left
this marriage,

00:12:54.530 --> 00:12:56.050 align:middle line:90%
how am I going to do the money?

00:12:56.050 --> 00:12:57.440 align:middle line:90%
I've got debt.

00:12:57.440 --> 00:12:58.890 align:middle line:90%
We make up all those things.

00:12:58.890 --> 00:13:00.289 align:middle line:90%
I don't know how to speak.

00:13:00.289 --> 00:13:01.330 align:middle line:90%
I don't know how to sing.

00:13:01.330 --> 00:13:02.770 align:middle line:90%
I don't know how to do comedy.

00:13:02.770 --> 00:13:05.330 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I'm not pretty enough,
smart enough, good enough.

00:13:05.330 --> 00:13:06.370 align:middle line:90%
Maybe I'm too old.

00:13:06.370 --> 00:13:07.600 align:middle line:90%
Maybe I'm too young.

00:13:07.600 --> 00:13:10.480 align:middle line:84%
These are all the
excuses we use just

00:13:10.480 --> 00:13:13.980 align:middle line:84%
to not step fully into the
thing that we most want to do.

00:13:13.980 --> 00:13:15.890 align:middle line:84%
But we don't realize
that we're keeping

00:13:15.890 --> 00:13:19.300 align:middle line:84%
those paradigms in place
because we're not stepping out.

00:13:19.300 --> 00:13:21.780 align:middle line:84%
If we would step
out, then life as we

00:13:21.780 --> 00:13:23.440 align:middle line:84%
desire it would
actually show up.

00:13:23.440 --> 00:13:26.920 align:middle line:84%
And you're living proof of
that with what you do, yes?

00:13:26.920 --> 00:13:30.150 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: It seems so real,
those money problems and all

00:13:30.150 --> 00:13:32.420 align:middle line:90%
those excuses that we have.

00:13:32.420 --> 00:13:36.430 align:middle line:84%
And trusting this
invisible, intangible thing

00:13:36.430 --> 00:13:39.536 align:middle line:90%
that we can't see is a big step.

00:13:39.536 --> 00:13:40.660 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: It's a huge step.

00:13:40.660 --> 00:13:42.730 align:middle line:84%
But we all say I
want the miracles.

00:13:42.730 --> 00:13:44.170 align:middle line:90%
I want to believe in this.

00:13:44.170 --> 00:13:46.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to set my intentions.

00:13:46.050 --> 00:13:47.650 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do all of this.

00:13:47.650 --> 00:13:52.010 align:middle line:84%
If instead you understood
you are gods walking,

00:13:52.010 --> 00:13:55.330 align:middle line:84%
you are pieces of
the divine-- and what

00:13:55.330 --> 00:13:58.802 align:middle line:84%
right do you have to hold
back the divine from fully

00:13:58.802 --> 00:13:59.760 align:middle line:90%
expressing through you?

00:13:59.760 --> 00:14:01.370 align:middle line:90%
What right do any of us have?

00:14:01.370 --> 00:14:03.640 align:middle line:84%
I think that's really
arrogant that we

00:14:03.640 --> 00:14:07.740 align:middle line:84%
think we can decide
to not fully express,

00:14:07.740 --> 00:14:09.780 align:middle line:84%
because that is what
is being asked of us.

00:14:09.780 --> 00:14:12.750 align:middle line:84%
And then we want to understand
why marriages aren't working

00:14:12.750 --> 00:14:15.620 align:middle line:84%
or why our jobs
are not fulfilling

00:14:15.620 --> 00:14:18.060 align:middle line:84%
or why the economy and
the health care system

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:20.110 align:middle line:84%
and everything else
is breaking down.

00:14:20.110 --> 00:14:22.030 align:middle line:84%
It's because it's
trying to get you

00:14:22.030 --> 00:14:24.750 align:middle line:84%
up and out of this conformity
that you've locked yourself

00:14:24.750 --> 00:14:25.650 align:middle line:90%
into.

00:14:25.650 --> 00:14:27.810 align:middle line:84%
Because life knows
you're more, and it's

00:14:27.810 --> 00:14:29.890 align:middle line:84%
trying to get you to
see that you're more.

00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:32.860 align:middle line:84%
But until you decide
I'm willing to step

00:14:32.860 --> 00:14:35.400 align:middle line:84%
into it despite the
fear, I'm willing to step

00:14:35.400 --> 00:14:38.660 align:middle line:84%
into it despite the excuses,
I'm willing to step into it

00:14:38.660 --> 00:14:42.040 align:middle line:84%
to see if I truly can trust the
universe, you'll never know.

00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:43.415 align:middle line:84%
And what you're
going to discover

00:14:43.415 --> 00:14:45.250 align:middle line:84%
is the universe
has got your back.

00:14:45.250 --> 00:14:47.750 align:middle line:84%
Every sign and
symbol will show up

00:14:47.750 --> 00:14:49.830 align:middle line:90%
to keep guiding you on your way.

00:14:49.830 --> 00:14:51.940 align:middle line:90%
But a conversation takes two.

00:14:51.940 --> 00:14:53.860 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is
the universe sends us

00:14:53.860 --> 00:14:57.220 align:middle line:84%
the signs and the symbols,
but then we say, um,

00:14:57.220 --> 00:15:00.242 align:middle line:84%
could you send me another symbol
so I can make sure I got it?

00:15:00.242 --> 00:15:02.200 align:middle line:84%
And then we get the next
symbol, and it's like,

00:15:02.200 --> 00:15:03.100 align:middle line:90%
OK, send me one more.

00:15:03.100 --> 00:15:04.560 align:middle line:84%
I need to get one
more symbol just

00:15:04.560 --> 00:15:06.500 align:middle line:84%
to make sure I know
what you're telling me.

00:15:06.500 --> 00:15:10.110 align:middle line:84%
If instead we would stop in the
moment that we get the symbol

00:15:10.110 --> 00:15:11.710 align:middle line:84%
and close our eyes
and take a breath

00:15:11.710 --> 00:15:14.640 align:middle line:84%
and see what we're really
thinking about in that moment

00:15:14.640 --> 00:15:17.220 align:middle line:84%
and follow our heart
as opposed to our head,

00:15:17.220 --> 00:15:20.700 align:middle line:84%
step out of logicalness,
step out of practicality,

00:15:20.700 --> 00:15:23.890 align:middle line:84%
follow the heart, that
is the communication back

00:15:23.890 --> 00:15:27.230 align:middle line:84%
in conversation that lets
the universe know to send you

00:15:27.230 --> 00:15:29.510 align:middle line:84%
the next symbol, the next
sign, the next doorway,

00:15:29.510 --> 00:15:31.110 align:middle line:90%
the next opportunity.

00:15:31.110 --> 00:15:32.710 align:middle line:90%
And then it will send you those.

00:15:32.710 --> 00:15:35.470 align:middle line:84%
And then you are to take
another step, large or small,

00:15:35.470 --> 00:15:38.280 align:middle line:84%
but some step to
be a conversation.

00:15:38.280 --> 00:15:40.880 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise there's only
one person talking or one

00:15:40.880 --> 00:15:42.720 align:middle line:84%
being talking, and
that's the universe.

00:15:42.720 --> 00:15:44.130 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:15:44.130 --> 00:15:45.710 align:middle line:10%
That fear, though,
sometimes it's

00:15:45.710 --> 00:15:49.300 align:middle line:10%
difficult to know the difference
between the fear and the heart

00:15:49.300 --> 00:15:51.420 align:middle line:10%
talking or the
intuition and all that.

00:15:51.420 --> 00:15:52.690 align:middle line:10%
How do you know?

00:15:52.690 --> 00:15:55.950 align:middle line:10%
Because we can feel
guilty or this and that.

00:15:55.950 --> 00:15:58.100 align:middle line:10%
Some things come up.

00:15:58.100 --> 00:16:00.770 align:middle line:10%
>> SINGH: I tell people if
you truly want to know what

00:16:00.770 --> 00:16:04.100 align:middle line:10%
the truth is, every time you
have to have a discussion with

00:16:04.100 --> 00:16:06.960 align:middle line:10%
yourself or go into the
mind about something,

00:16:06.960 --> 00:16:09.660 align:middle line:10%
if you will disconnect the
brain by closing your eyes,

00:16:09.660 --> 00:16:12.730 align:middle line:10%
take a deep breath, and then
ask that question to yourself,

00:16:12.730 --> 00:16:15.630 align:middle line:10%
and the very first answer that
comes to mind is the truth

00:16:15.630 --> 00:16:16.170 align:middle line:10%
of you.

00:16:16.170 --> 00:16:17.360 align:middle line:90%
It will always happen.

00:16:17.360 --> 00:16:19.290 align:middle line:84%
It will never fail
you, because you

00:16:19.290 --> 00:16:21.230 align:middle line:84%
have an inherent
wisdom within you.

00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:22.860 align:middle line:90%
We all have that.

00:16:22.860 --> 00:16:26.390 align:middle line:84%
The problem is we're walking
around as talking heads,

00:16:26.390 --> 00:16:28.280 align:middle line:84%
and we need to drop
from here down.

00:16:28.280 --> 00:16:30.450 align:middle line:84%
If we close our eyes,
close off the brain,

00:16:30.450 --> 00:16:32.390 align:middle line:84%
and listen to the
heart and the gut,

00:16:32.390 --> 00:16:34.560 align:middle line:84%
we're going to get
every answer we want.

00:16:34.560 --> 00:16:36.280 align:middle line:84%
And then the
universe will supply

00:16:36.280 --> 00:16:38.850 align:middle line:84%
the responses to
open those doors.

00:16:38.850 --> 00:16:40.860 align:middle line:84%
And we've seen
that in our lives.

00:16:40.860 --> 00:16:43.450 align:middle line:84%
We've each leapt out
on full faith and trust

00:16:43.450 --> 00:16:46.740 align:middle line:84%
to know that I don't have
everything I need to do this,

00:16:46.740 --> 00:16:49.750 align:middle line:84%
but there's a calling inside
of me that will not stop,

00:16:49.750 --> 00:16:51.760 align:middle line:90%
and I'm going to do this anyway.

00:16:51.760 --> 00:16:54.255 align:middle line:84%
And let me let the
universe help me.

00:16:54.255 --> 00:16:56.370 align:middle line:84%
Let me let the
universe assist me.

00:16:56.370 --> 00:17:00.940 align:middle line:84%
This is a time about allowing,
not willing, not trying,

00:17:00.940 --> 00:17:02.130 align:middle line:90%
not toiling.

00:17:02.130 --> 00:17:06.880 align:middle line:84%
This is all about now allowing
the universe to fully unfold.

00:17:06.880 --> 00:17:10.260 align:middle line:84%
And I think for most of us we've
been trying to drive the car,

00:17:10.260 --> 00:17:12.790 align:middle line:84%
and we've told the
universe, source, or God

00:17:12.790 --> 00:17:15.599 align:middle line:84%
to sit in the passenger seat
and telling it where to go.

00:17:15.599 --> 00:17:18.246 align:middle line:84%
Instead, we need to move over
and let the universe drive.

00:17:18.246 --> 00:17:20.579 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: Even though if it
feels like we're blindfolded

00:17:20.579 --> 00:17:23.000 align:middle line:90%
and can't see anything?

00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:24.379 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: We're blind anyway.

00:17:24.379 --> 00:17:25.369 align:middle line:90%
We're blind anyway.

00:17:25.369 --> 00:17:28.540 align:middle line:84%
We're all blind, dumb, and deaf
as we walk through this life.

00:17:28.540 --> 00:17:30.650 align:middle line:84%
That's why we have no
idea what we're doing.

00:17:30.650 --> 00:17:33.710 align:middle line:84%
So if we're already
that, then we

00:17:33.710 --> 00:17:37.250 align:middle line:90%
can't worry about messing up.

00:17:37.250 --> 00:17:39.430 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
the biggest thing.

00:17:39.430 --> 00:17:42.420 align:middle line:84%
People are too concerned
about making a mistake.

00:17:42.420 --> 00:17:44.220 align:middle line:90%
What if there are no mistakes?

00:17:44.220 --> 00:17:45.860 align:middle line:90%
What if there's no wrong turns?

00:17:45.860 --> 00:17:48.130 align:middle line:84%
What if you can't
possibly do it wrong

00:17:48.130 --> 00:17:50.900 align:middle line:84%
but every single step,
regardless of your choice,

00:17:50.900 --> 00:17:53.230 align:middle line:84%
actually takes you
to exactly where you

00:17:53.230 --> 00:17:56.870 align:middle line:84%
need to go for either the
next training or the purpose

00:17:56.870 --> 00:17:58.380 align:middle line:90%
that you were intended to be?

00:17:58.380 --> 00:18:00.780 align:middle line:84%
And there really is only
one purpose in life,

00:18:00.780 --> 00:18:04.760 align:middle line:84%
and that is to have
experience experience itself.

00:18:04.760 --> 00:18:06.660 align:middle line:84%
That is the only
purpose for all of us,

00:18:06.660 --> 00:18:11.100 align:middle line:84%
to be constant creative capacity
and to live as children.

00:18:11.100 --> 00:18:13.160 align:middle line:84%
We've forgotten
how children are.

00:18:13.160 --> 00:18:15.930 align:middle line:84%
And that's what your journey to
enlightenment really focuses on

00:18:15.930 --> 00:18:19.970 align:middle line:84%
is teaching us how to play
and go back into that essence

00:18:19.970 --> 00:18:22.720 align:middle line:84%
that children have, because
they're natural manifestors.

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:23.910 align:middle line:90%
They live in the now.

00:18:23.910 --> 00:18:25.497 align:middle line:90%
They know how to do that.

00:18:25.497 --> 00:18:26.330 align:middle line:90%
And we've forgotten.

00:18:26.330 --> 00:18:28.150 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:18:28.150 --> 00:18:30.840 align:middle line:90%
My goodness.

00:18:30.840 --> 00:18:35.210 align:middle line:84%
Is there practical things
that we can do, for you, even,

00:18:35.210 --> 00:18:36.510 align:middle line:90%
