3-year-old right now,

00:25:29.840 --> 00:25:34.110 align:middle line:84%
is they're so present to their
feeling and their expression.

00:25:34.110 --> 00:25:36.230 align:middle line:84%
When you see a
child, they can be

00:25:36.230 --> 00:25:39.550 align:middle line:84%
in a full-out tantrum for two
or three minutes, and then

00:25:39.550 --> 00:25:41.960 align:middle line:84%
all of a sudden an
airplane will fly by

00:25:41.960 --> 00:25:44.450 align:middle line:84%
and they will be up
cruising the grounds

00:25:44.450 --> 00:25:46.660 align:middle line:84%
like an airplane
giggling and laughing.

00:25:46.660 --> 00:25:48.650 align:middle line:84%
They don't carry
anything with them.

00:25:48.650 --> 00:25:50.350 align:middle line:84%
If they're on a
playground, they're

00:25:50.350 --> 00:25:53.590 align:middle line:84%
not sliding down the slide
fully immersed in the slide

00:25:53.590 --> 00:25:55.845 align:middle line:84%
and then see the merry-go-round
and pick up the slide

00:25:55.845 --> 00:25:57.220 align:middle line:84%
and put it on
their back and then

00:25:57.220 --> 00:25:58.830 align:middle line:90%
go play on the merry-go-round.

00:25:58.830 --> 00:26:00.260 align:middle line:90%
But that's what we do.

00:26:00.260 --> 00:26:01.954 align:middle line:84%
We have an
experience, and rather

00:26:01.954 --> 00:26:04.120 align:middle line:84%
than leaving the experience,
feeling the experience,

00:26:04.120 --> 00:26:06.480 align:middle line:84%
and moving on to the next
one, we pick it up and put it

00:26:06.480 --> 00:26:09.045 align:middle line:84%
on our backs and we carry
it to the next thing.

00:26:09.045 --> 00:26:10.670 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of
things that children

00:26:10.670 --> 00:26:12.940 align:middle line:84%
come in teaching us
right from the beginning,

00:26:12.940 --> 00:26:15.170 align:middle line:84%
and those are the essences
that I talk about.

00:26:15.170 --> 00:26:18.120 align:middle line:10%
If we just tap into
those 12 essences,

00:26:18.120 --> 00:26:21.440 align:middle line:10%
we return to the child,
we return to play,

00:26:21.440 --> 00:26:23.240 align:middle line:10%
we return to lightening up.

00:26:23.240 --> 00:26:26.150 align:middle line:10%
We have forgotten who
we are because we've

00:26:26.150 --> 00:26:27.310 align:middle line:10%
gotten too serious.

00:26:27.310 --> 00:26:29.630 align:middle line:10%
We've gotten way too serious
about life and everything

00:26:29.630 --> 00:26:30.130 align:middle line:10%
in life.

00:26:30.130 --> 00:26:33.270 align:middle line:10%
Even our spirituality, we've
made it way too serious.

00:26:33.270 --> 00:26:35.430 align:middle line:10%
And if we can
understand that there's

00:26:35.430 --> 00:26:38.690 align:middle line:10%
a seventh sense
beyond intuition,

00:26:38.690 --> 00:26:40.291 align:middle line:10%
it is the sense
of humor, and that

00:26:40.291 --> 00:26:41.915 align:middle line:10%
is the one that leads
to enlightenment.

00:26:41.915 --> 00:26:42.970 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:26:42.970 --> 00:26:43.788 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Yeah.

00:26:43.788 --> 00:26:45.246 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: You're
Indian originally.

00:26:45.246 --> 00:26:46.200 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Yes.

00:26:46.200 --> 00:26:49.350 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: I'm sure some of
us and I'm thinking, yeah,

00:26:49.350 --> 00:26:49.885 align:middle line:90%
it's easy.

00:26:49.885 --> 00:26:51.250 align:middle line:90%
You were born in this.

00:26:51.250 --> 00:26:52.962 align:middle line:90%
You've got that.

00:26:52.962 --> 00:26:54.670 align:middle line:84%
But you were not always
like this, right?

00:26:54.670 --> 00:26:57.947 align:middle line:84%
You grew up in different
states in the United States--

00:26:57.947 --> 00:26:58.530 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Yes.

00:26:58.530 --> 00:27:01.470 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: --and you
really went the other way,

00:27:01.470 --> 00:27:04.900 align:middle line:84%
like workaholic and
this and that, right?

00:27:04.900 --> 00:27:07.450 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: Oh, the universe
has a huge sense of humor.

00:27:07.450 --> 00:27:09.720 align:middle line:84%
It really knows how to
create a practical joke.

00:27:09.720 --> 00:27:13.390 align:middle line:84%
I was planted in the Bible Belt
South, Indian woman preaching

00:27:13.390 --> 00:27:15.450 align:middle line:84%
spirituality in the
Bible Belt South.

00:27:15.450 --> 00:27:18.450 align:middle line:84%
What's a bigger joke
than that, right?

00:27:18.450 --> 00:27:20.230 align:middle line:84%
But I did all the
things that most of us

00:27:20.230 --> 00:27:24.760 align:middle line:84%
do, people please, try to
numb out in some sort of way.

00:27:24.760 --> 00:27:27.340 align:middle line:84%
Workaholism was my
way to numb out.

00:27:27.340 --> 00:27:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And I know that there's one
commonality between all of us.

00:27:31.060 --> 00:27:34.330 align:middle line:84%
None of us want to feel pain,
and we each want to be loved.

00:27:34.330 --> 00:27:35.940 align:middle line:84%
But until we get
to the place where

00:27:35.940 --> 00:27:38.430 align:middle line:84%
we're fully able to
give love to ourselves,

00:27:38.430 --> 00:27:40.390 align:middle line:84%
we'll keep creating
the place that we

00:27:40.390 --> 00:27:41.890 align:middle line:90%
become the walking dead.

00:27:41.890 --> 00:27:43.960 align:middle line:84%
And life has to
crash at some point,

00:27:43.960 --> 00:27:45.770 align:middle line:90%
if that's the road were on.

00:27:45.770 --> 00:27:47.140 align:middle line:90%
But that too is light.

00:27:47.140 --> 00:27:48.730 align:middle line:84%
Because you can't
see light in light.

00:27:48.730 --> 00:27:50.420 align:middle line:90%
You have to have the dark.

00:27:50.420 --> 00:27:53.270 align:middle line:84%
And so when that happens,
we then start the rise.

00:27:53.270 --> 00:27:55.310 align:middle line:84%
And we rise into
love in a way where

00:27:55.310 --> 00:27:58.420 align:middle line:84%
we start to discover
how to treat ourselves,

00:27:58.420 --> 00:28:01.337 align:middle line:84%
how to carry ourselves,
how to honor ourselves.

00:28:01.337 --> 00:28:03.170 align:middle line:84%
And when that happens,
the rest of the world

00:28:03.170 --> 00:28:04.724 align:middle line:90%
starts to do the same.

00:28:04.724 --> 00:28:07.140 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: From the moment you
made that decision and there

00:28:07.140 --> 00:28:12.930 align:middle line:84%
was this change and the prayer
and the signs of the 11's, did

00:28:12.930 --> 00:28:14.770 align:middle line:90%
it evolve?

00:28:14.770 --> 00:28:17.970 align:middle line:84%
How did it evolve, this
journey, from really starting

00:28:17.970 --> 00:28:20.205 align:middle line:84%
to see those symbols
to where you are now?

00:28:20.205 --> 00:28:22.890 align:middle line:90%


00:28:22.890 --> 00:28:25.830 align:middle line:84%
You can tell us, if you
want, where you're at now.

00:28:25.830 --> 00:28:30.810 align:middle line:84%
It's quite an example of how to
just trust and be with what's

00:28:30.810 --> 00:28:33.270 align:middle line:90%
so and all is well, you know?

00:28:33.270 --> 00:28:33.970 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Yes.

00:28:33.970 --> 00:28:37.850 align:middle line:84%
When I had my initial time
on my prayer room floor,

00:28:37.850 --> 00:28:40.120 align:middle line:84%
I realized that
something had to change.

00:28:40.120 --> 00:28:42.750 align:middle line:84%
And the common denominator in
my life where all the pain was

00:28:42.750 --> 00:28:43.870 align:middle line:90%
was me.

00:28:43.870 --> 00:28:45.910 align:middle line:84%
So I was the one
that had to shift.

00:28:45.910 --> 00:28:49.490 align:middle line:84%
And the five questions that
I stipulate in "Conversations

00:28:49.490 --> 00:28:52.320 align:middle line:84%
with the Universe" are how
I began to live my life.

00:28:52.320 --> 00:28:54.820 align:middle line:84%
Every single thing that
showed up in my world,

00:28:54.820 --> 00:28:57.110 align:middle line:84%
I just chose to
believe that's me.

00:28:57.110 --> 00:28:57.690 align:middle line:90%
That's me.

00:28:57.690 --> 00:29:00.250 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's good,
bad, or ugly, it's me.

00:29:00.250 --> 00:29:02.300 align:middle line:84%
So if it's me,
where is it in here?

00:29:02.300 --> 00:29:06.130 align:middle line:84%
And until I find how I do that
to myself or someone else,

00:29:06.130 --> 00:29:08.350 align:middle line:84%
I will not stop this
cleaning and clearing.

00:29:08.350 --> 00:29:10.350 align:middle line:84%
And over the course
of my life, I

00:29:10.350 --> 00:29:13.550 align:middle line:84%
began cleaning so much
of my interior landscape

00:29:13.550 --> 00:29:15.510 align:middle line:84%
that doors just
opened automatically,

00:29:15.510 --> 00:29:17.700 align:middle line:84%
things happened
automatically, because that's

00:29:17.700 --> 00:29:19.340 align:middle line:90%
the magical way of the universe.

00:29:19.340 --> 00:29:23.780 align:middle line:84%
The more we align to our truth,
the more truth gives us back.

00:29:23.780 --> 00:29:27.650 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: When you say
clearing, you clear it?

00:29:27.650 --> 00:29:28.640 align:middle line:90%
You speak out?

00:29:28.640 --> 00:29:30.750 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: Yes, feeling
it, mostly feeling it.

00:29:30.750 --> 00:29:34.010 align:middle line:84%
For me, I was so numbed out
I wouldn't feel anything.

00:29:34.010 --> 00:29:37.320 align:middle line:84%
I had not ever cried in my
life until I was 38 years old.

00:29:37.320 --> 00:29:39.190 align:middle line:84%
That was the first
time I ever cried.

00:29:39.190 --> 00:29:42.890 align:middle line:84%
And so I had to get in touch
with what emotion even was,

00:29:42.890 --> 00:29:44.280 align:middle line:90%
and it took time.

00:29:44.280 --> 00:29:47.570 align:middle line:84%
And I allowed myself that
time to dive into the shadows,

00:29:47.570 --> 00:29:51.150 align:middle line:84%
to dive into the pain, to
really sit and immerse in that.

00:29:51.150 --> 00:29:54.480 align:middle line:84%
Because children understand
that that's beautiful too.

00:29:54.480 --> 00:29:57.510 align:middle line:84%
They full-out experience
it, but we don't.

00:29:57.510 --> 00:30:00.440 align:middle line:84%
So I decided I'm going to
full-out experience all of it.

00:30:00.440 --> 00:30:03.350 align:middle line:84%
Because the only way it can get
out of you is to experience it.

00:30:03.350 --> 00:30:06.000 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise we suppress it
and push it back down.

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:08.760 align:middle line:84%
And then it stays with us,
recreating reincarnations

00:30:08.760 --> 00:30:12.040 align:middle line:84%
of the same experiences
again and again and again.

00:30:12.040 --> 00:30:13.840 align:middle line:90%
And so that's what I did.

00:30:13.840 --> 00:30:16.980 align:middle line:84%
And when I finally got the
courage to leave my marriage

00:30:16.980 --> 00:30:20.920 align:middle line:84%
and this Rebel Road idea
came, the spontaneity

00:30:20.920 --> 00:30:24.780 align:middle line:84%
of getting on stage not
having any clue what I'm doing

00:30:24.780 --> 00:30:28.740 align:middle line:84%
and not being perfect-- the
very first show that I went to

00:30:28.740 --> 00:30:31.935 align:middle line:84%
in DC, I forgot the
verses of two songs.

00:30:31.935 --> 00:30:33.810 align:middle line:84%
And I just stood there
and let the music play

00:30:33.810 --> 00:30:35.518 align:middle line:84%
and told the audience
I've just forgotten

00:30:35.518 --> 00:30:38.790 align:middle line:84%
the verses of two songs, because
that was all I knew how to do.

00:30:38.790 --> 00:30:42.040 align:middle line:84%
It was me being intimate and
vulnerable and authentic.

00:30:42.040 --> 00:30:43.850 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of
that show, five people

00:30:43.850 --> 00:30:45.530 align:middle line:84%
came up and said the
same thing to me.

00:30:45.530 --> 00:30:48.490 align:middle line:84%
But one in particular is the
one that I remember the most.

00:30:48.490 --> 00:30:50.410 align:middle line:84%
She was an opera
singer, and she had

00:30:50.410 --> 00:30:52.820 align:middle line:84%
been invited to tour the
world four times by four

00:30:52.820 --> 00:30:54.760 align:middle line:84%
different companies,
and she turned them

00:30:54.760 --> 00:30:56.600 align:middle line:90%
down each and every time.

00:30:56.600 --> 00:30:59.040 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I want to thank
you for what you're doing.

00:30:59.040 --> 00:31:02.000 align:middle line:84%
It has inspired me greatly,
because my greatest fear

00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:03.460 align:middle line:84%
was that I would
forget the words.

00:31:03.460 --> 00:31:05.580 align:middle line:84%
And you've just shown
me how to do that.

00:31:05.580 --> 00:31:08.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go be an opera
singer and tour the world.

00:31:08.020 --> 00:31:11.200 align:middle line:84%
And I have had more stories
of different situations

00:31:11.200 --> 00:31:14.120 align:middle line:84%
because I was willing to be
real and willing to show people

00:31:14.120 --> 00:31:15.860 align:middle line:84%
we're not supposed
to have it perfect.

00:31:15.860 --> 00:31:17.370 align:middle line:84%
I didn't need to
know how to sing,

00:31:17.370 --> 00:31:19.350 align:middle line:84%
because by the end
of 66 shows, I'd

00:31:19.350 --> 00:31:20.700 align:middle line:90%
figure out how to sing, right?

00:31:20.700 --> 00:31:23.440 align:middle line:84%
It's experience
experiencing itself.

00:31:23.440 --> 00:31:26.240 align:middle line:84%
So get off this perfection
bandwagon or thinking

00:31:26.240 --> 00:31:28.330 align:middle line:84%
that you have to get it
right before you start.

00:31:28.330 --> 00:31:30.140 align:middle line:90%
I believe in quality.

00:31:30.140 --> 00:31:32.030 align:middle line:84%
But right now we
are in an age that

00:31:32.030 --> 00:31:35.010 align:middle line:84%
is more about experience
and expression.

00:31:35.010 --> 00:31:37.200 align:middle line:84%
Before that, the age
was not about that.

00:31:37.200 --> 00:31:39.130 align:middle line:84%
It was about
accomplishment, attainment.

00:31:39.130 --> 00:31:41.310 align:middle line:90%
We are now about experience.

00:31:41.310 --> 00:31:43.240 align:middle line:90%
And experience has no agenda.

00:31:43.240 --> 00:31:44.600 align:middle line:90%
It has no outcome.

00:31:44.600 --> 00:31:46.580 align:middle line:84%
It's not about filling
up a bunch of seats,

00:31:46.580 --> 00:31:49.520 align:middle line:84%
selling a bunch of products,
or filling up a bank account.

00:31:49.520 --> 00:31:53.930 align:middle line:84%
Experience is about filling you
up, standing in your own seat,

00:31:53.930 --> 00:31:57.240 align:middle line:84%
and finding the abundance and
wealth that you possess inside.

00:31:57.240 --> 00:31:58.500 align:middle line:90%
That's where we are now.

00:31:58.500 --> 00:32:00.610 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:32:00.610 --> 00:32:06.570 align:middle line:84%
You have to tell us about the RV
story and the graphic designer

00:32:06.570 --> 00:32:07.836 align:middle line:90%
before that--

00:32:07.836 --> 00:32:09.450 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Yes.

00:32:09.450 --> 00:32:13.410 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: --and also that you
decided to turn off the prices

00:32:13.410 --> 00:32:14.810 align:middle line:90%
on your website.

00:32:14.810 --> 00:32:18.520 align:middle line:84%
Those are really big
bold stories, three

00:32:18.520 --> 00:32:21.190 align:middle line:84%
beautiful examples, I think,
and you probably have some more,

00:32:21.190 --> 00:32:22.630 align:middle line:90%
I'm sure.

00:32:22.630 --> 00:32:25.500 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: I have six months'
worth of full-out sign symbol

00:32:25.500 --> 00:32:27.840 align:middle line:84%
stories that I've been
creating a show with.

00:32:27.840 --> 00:32:29.800 align:middle line:84%
And I have received
guidance lately

00:32:29.800 --> 00:32:31.130 align:middle line:90%
to change how I do things.

00:32:31.130 --> 00:32:32.920 align:middle line:84%
I've always given
"11:11 Magazine" away

00:32:32.920 --> 00:32:34.790 align:middle line:84%
and the radio show
away, but now I'm

00:32:34.790 --> 00:32:38.470 align:middle line:84%
being guided to give it all
away in a way that people choose

00:32:38.470 --> 00:32:40.350 align:middle line:84%
the value of it,
rather than me saying,

00:32:40.350 --> 00:32:41.910 align:middle line:84%
this is how much
it's going to be.

00:32:41.910 --> 00:32:44.770 align:middle line:84%
It's to help shift this
economic paradigm that we're in,

00:32:44.770 --> 00:32:47.120 align:middle line:84%
to start to say there are
other forms of exchange

00:32:47.120 --> 00:32:49.330 align:middle line:84%
and there are new ways
for us to do things,

00:32:49.330 --> 00:32:50.740 align:middle line:84%
but we each have
to take the step

00:32:50.740 --> 00:32:53.750 align:middle line:84%
of being that example for
the world to really change.

00:32:53.750 --> 00:32:57.469 align:middle line:84%
As I began this Rebel Road
tour, I got the vision

00:32:57.469 --> 00:32:59.010 align:middle line:84%
that everything was
going to show up,

00:32:59.010 --> 00:33:01.970 align:middle line:84%
the RV, that I would be
invited to 66 cities,

00:33:01.970 --> 00:33:05.320 align:middle line:84%
that I was not to plan it, to
control it, to do anything.

00:33:05.320 --> 00:33:08.540 align:middle line:84%
And three weeks before I
was to leave in September,

00:33:08.540 --> 00:33:10.010 align:middle line:90%
an RV appeared.

00:33:10.010 --> 00:33:12.560 align:middle line:84%
One week before I was
supposed to leave we

00:33:12.560 --> 00:33:15.455 align:middle line:84%
already had 42 places
that had invited me.

00:33:15.455 --> 00:33:16.080 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:33:16.080 --> 00:33:18.405 align:middle line:84%
And I just want to say
this is with two children.

00:33:18.405 --> 00:33:20.480 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: I have two children,
a 3-year-old and a 12-year-old.

00:33:20.480 --> 00:33:21.490 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Single mom.

00:33:21.490 --> 00:33:22.290 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Yes.

00:33:22.290 --> 00:33:23.900 align:middle line:84%
We have been in a
little Petri dish

00:33:23.900 --> 00:33:28.550 align:middle line:84%
in this 1991 refurbished RV
that is 31 foot by 7 foot.

00:33:28.550 --> 00:33:30.690 align:middle line:84%
There's been five of
us living in there.

00:33:30.690 --> 00:33:33.500 align:middle line:84%
And talk about a Petri dish
to discover relationship

00:33:33.500 --> 00:33:36.500 align:middle line:84%
and to discover how
we interact truly.

00:33:36.500 --> 00:33:38.170 align:middle line:90%
But isn't that what life is?

00:33:38.170 --> 00:33:39.670 align:middle line:84%
We're not supposed
to run from that.

00:33:39.670 --> 00:33:41.470 align:middle line:84%
We're supposed to dive
into it, because that's

00:33:41.470 --> 00:33:43.080 align:middle line:84%
where you become
self-realized, where

00:33:43.080 --> 00:33:44.910 align:middle line:84%
you see when your
shadows are triggered.

00:33:44.910 --> 00:33:47.880 align:middle line:84%
And it's amazing what you
discover about yourself

00:33:47.880 --> 00:33:49.350 align:middle line:90%
when you're in small quarters.

00:33:49.350 --> 00:33:53.570 align:middle line:84%
And it's amazing to discover
how little we really need,

00:33:53.570 --> 00:33:54.240 align:middle line:90%
how little.

00:33:54.240 --> 00:33:56.685 align:middle line:84%
We live in such excess,
and we don't need to.

00:33:56.685 --> 00:33:57.310 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:33:57.310 --> 00:33:59.520 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: And so there've
been things like that.

00:33:59.520 --> 00:34:01.480 align:middle line:84%
But I will share one
really profound story,

00:34:01.480 --> 00:34:02.620 align:middle line:90%
just to show people--

00:34:02.620 --> 00:34:06.220 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: As we have the
Miami music in the background.

00:34:06.220 --> 00:34:07.696 align:middle line:90%
And they're dancing.

00:34:07.696 --> 00:34:09.480 align:middle line:84%
I wish I could turn
the camera around.

00:34:09.480 --> 00:34:10.980 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: Because
that's who we are,

00:34:10.980 --> 00:34:14.920 align:middle line:84%
signs and symbols showing
up right now, right?

00:34:14.920 --> 00:34:19.300 align:middle line:84%
But as I was on the road, when
we just left South Carolina,

00:34:19.300 --> 00:34:22.070 align:middle line:84%
we got within two hours, and
I had to fill up with gas.

00:34:22.070 --> 00:34:24.199 align:middle line:84%
And the RV wouldn't
crank back up,

00:34:24.199 --> 00:34:25.792 align:middle line:90%
and so I had to be jump-started.

00:34:25.792 --> 00:34:28.000 align:middle line:84%
And we got to the next
campground to spend the night.

00:34:28.000 --> 00:34:29.800 align:middle line:84%
The next morning
we were to leave,

00:34:29.800 --> 00:34:31.530 align:middle line:90%
and the RV wouldn't start again.

00:34:31.530 --> 00:34:34.460 align:middle line:84%
So we had to go to a
station to get it worked on.

00:34:34.460 --> 00:34:37.030 align:middle line:84%
While I was there, the
gentleman there in Fayetteville,

00:34:37.030 --> 00:34:39.730 align:middle line:84%
North Carolina, the
largest murder capital

00:34:39.730 --> 00:34:41.560 align:middle line:84%
in the United States
right now, wanted

00:34:41.560 --> 00:34:43.070 align:middle line:84%
to know what the
word rebel meant.

00:34:43.070 --> 00:34:44.929 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people
question that word.

00:34:44.929 --> 00:34:46.820 align:middle line:84%
And so I explained
to them about there

00:34:46.820 --> 00:34:48.770 align:middle line:84%
being no fight outside,
no fight inside.

00:34:48.770 --> 00:34:50.739 align:middle line:84%
This is about peace,
love, and oneness.

00:34:50.739 --> 00:34:52.719 align:middle line:84%
And they fixed my
RV and found out

00:34:52.719 --> 00:34:54.989 align:middle line:84%
it was a piece
called the solenoid.

00:34:54.989 --> 00:34:58.040 align:middle line:84%
The solenoid is a communication
box between the ignition

00:34:58.040 --> 00:35:00.126 align:middle line:84%
and the engine of
a vehicle, so it

00:35:00.126 --> 00:35:02.000 align:middle line:84%
tells the engine when
you've inserted the key

00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:03.125 align:middle line:90%
and you've cranked it up.

00:35:03.125 --> 00:35:05.770 align:middle line:84%
I was expecting a
$600 or $700 bill.

00:35:05.770 --> 00:35:07.920 align:middle line:84%
It was not exactly how I
wanted to start this tour,

00:35:07.920 --> 00:35:09.630 align:middle line:90%
but it was what it was.

00:35:09.630 --> 00:35:12.760 align:middle line:84%
And so when they finished,
the mechanic came to the door

00:35:12.760 --> 00:35:16.230 align:middle line:84%
and he handed me $200
and a business card.

00:35:16.230 --> 00:35:18.090 align:middle line:84%
And he said, the person
you were speaking

00:35:18.090 --> 00:35:20.940 align:middle line:84%
to about the word rebel was the
owner of this establishment.

00:35:20.940 --> 00:35:23.110 align:middle line:84%
He's completely inspired
by what you're doing.

00:35:23.110 --> 00:35:25.250 align:middle line:84%
He's waiving all
charges for fixing this.

00:35:25.250 --> 00:35:28.420 align:middle line:84%
He wants to donate
$200 to your cause,

00:35:28.420 --> 00:35:30.052 align:middle line:90%
and here's his business card.

00:35:30.052 --> 00:35:31.510 align:middle line:84%
And I looked at
the business card--

00:35:31.510 --> 00:35:33.250 align:middle line:84%
now Lilou, if you
had seen these men,

00:35:33.250 --> 00:35:36.000 align:middle line:84%
these were burly man with
grizzly beards, sweaty,

00:35:36.000 --> 00:35:37.530 align:middle line:90%
with oil on them.

00:35:37.530 --> 00:35:40.680 align:middle line:84%
His name was Jim
Souls, S-O-U-L-S,

00:35:40.680 --> 00:35:43.590 align:middle line:84%
and there was a pair of angel
wings on the top of his card.

00:35:43.590 --> 00:35:45.790 align:middle line:84%
Look at how the
universe provides.

00:35:45.790 --> 00:35:47.520 align:middle line:84%
So we left there and
went to DC, where

00:35:47.520 --> 00:35:48.811 align:middle line:90%
the first show was going to be.

00:35:48.811 --> 00:35:51.130 align:middle line:84%
And I got to the campground,
went inside to the office,

00:35:51.130 --> 00:35:53.760 align:middle line:84%
came back out, and
the RV wouldn't crank.

00:35:53.760 --> 00:35:55.620 align:middle line:84%
So I had to get it
jump-started again.

00:35:55.620 --> 00:35:57.820 align:middle line:84%
We got to our parking
place, I turned

00:35:57.820 --> 00:35:59.310 align:middle line:84%
it off, tried to
turn it back on.

00:35:59.310 --> 00:36:00.130 align:middle line:90%
It wouldn't crank.

00:36:00.130 --> 00:36:02.650 align:middle line:84%
So I said, universe, what
is you're trying to tell me?

00:36:02.650 --> 00:36:05.350 align:middle line:84%
I know I'm supposed to create
every show spontaneously.

00:36:05.350 --> 00:36:08.830 align:middle line:84%
What's the message you're
trying to get me to understand?

00:36:08.830 --> 00:36:12.650 align:middle line:84%
So I sat down, I took a breath,
and the first word that came in

00:36:12.650 --> 00:36:13.700 align:middle line:90%
was solenoid.

00:36:13.700 --> 00:36:17.590 align:middle line:84%
So I sat there and I said,
solenoid, solenoid, solenoid,

00:36:17.590 --> 00:36:19.710 align:middle line:84%
solenoid, silly
noise, silly noise.

00:36:19.710 --> 00:36:21.060 align:middle line:90%
Silly noise?

00:36:21.060 --> 00:36:23.360 align:middle line:84%
Is it the silly noise
that's all around us

00:36:23.360 --> 00:36:25.600 align:middle line:84%
and the silly noise
that's inside of us that

00:36:25.600 --> 00:36:28.130 align:middle line:84%
keeps us stopping and starting
and stopping and starting

00:36:28.130 --> 00:36:29.660 align:middle line:90%
so we don't live our dreams?

00:36:29.660 --> 00:36:31.200 align:middle line:84%
If that's the
message that you're

00:36:31.200 --> 00:36:34.430 align:middle line:84%
trying to get across to the
audience, please let the RV

00:36:34.430 --> 00:36:35.280 align:middle line:90%
crank.

00:36:35.280 --> 00:36:37.600 align:middle line:84%
And I got in the
driver's seat, and the RV

00:36:37.600 --> 00:36:40.420 align:middle line:84%
cranked and cranked
every show, every step

00:36:40.420 --> 00:36:42.090 align:middle line:90%
of the way for the first leg.

00:36:42.090 --> 00:36:46.060 align:middle line:84%
Now a lot of people would
say, OK, that's a coincidence.

00:36:46.060 --> 00:36:47.175 align:middle line:90%
It just was a loose wire.

00:36:47.175 --> 00:36:48.550 align:middle line:84%
Something kind of
happened there.

00:36:48.550 --> 00:36:50.570 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: Oh, you've got
many of those, though.

00:36:50.570 --> 00:36:52.840 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: But when we
left on the second leg,

00:36:52.840 --> 00:36:55.750 align:middle line:84%
I spoke to you earlier about a
personal issue that I'm going

00:36:55.750 --> 00:36:58.230 align:middle line:84%
through, and I happened to
stop by my parents' home,

00:36:58.230 --> 00:37:01.590 align:middle line:84%
and they said something to me
that kind of got me a little

00:37:01.590 --> 00:37:02.570 align:middle line:90%
jittery inside.

00:37:02.570 --> 00:37:05.330 align:middle line:84%
And I'm the kind of person
that 99% of the time I'm

00:37:05.330 --> 00:37:06.780 align:middle line:90%
in my happy place.

00:37:06.780 --> 00:37:09.180 align:middle line:84%
But all the way back to
Charleston to pack up the RV,

00:37:09.180 --> 00:37:11.360 align:middle line:84%
I was just feeling really
uncomfortable and jittery

00:37:11.360 --> 00:37:13.750 align:middle line:84%
and the stories were
going in my mind.

00:37:13.750 --> 00:37:16.720 align:middle line:84%
And I get there, we pack up
the RV, get ready to leave,

00:37:16.720 --> 00:37:18.520 align:middle line:90%
the RV won't crank.

00:37:18.520 --> 00:37:21.550 align:middle line:84%
And so I try 12 more
times, not even a click.

00:37:21.550 --> 00:37:23.310 align:middle line:84%
So I get in the car
and I tell the kids

00:37:23.310 --> 00:37:27.020 align:middle line:84%
and I tell my assistant, Tuck
we were going to go to a hotel.

00:37:27.020 --> 00:37:29.050 align:middle line:84%
I'll get this fixed
tomorrow, and we'll leave.

00:37:29.050 --> 00:37:31.085 align:middle line:84%
I'm about to put the
key in the ignition,

00:37:31.085 --> 00:37:33.060 align:middle line:90%
and I go, silly noise.

00:37:33.060 --> 00:37:34.920 align:middle line:84%
Oh my gosh, Tuck,
it's the silly noise.

00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:37.230 align:middle line:90%
I need to go try the RV again.

00:37:37.230 --> 00:37:39.174 align:middle line:84%
And I got in the RV,
and I said I'm not

00:37:39.174 --> 00:37:41.090 align:middle line:84%
buying into those things
I heard this morning.

00:37:41.090 --> 00:37:42.714 align:middle line:84%
I'm getting rid of
all that silly noise

00:37:42.714 --> 00:37:45.694 align:middle line:84%
because I know the
truth of this situation.

00:37:45.694 --> 00:37:47.610 align:middle line:84%
I put the key in the
ignition, the RV cranked,

00:37:47.610 --> 00:37:49.250 align:middle line:90%
and it has cranked ever since.

00:37:49.250 --> 00:37:52.670 align:middle line:84%
What if we are at that connected
to everything in our reality

00:37:52.670 --> 00:37:54.040 align:middle line:90%
and we don't even realize it?

00:37:54.040 --> 00:37:56.070 align:middle line:84%
What if everything
is simply there

00:37:56.070 --> 00:37:59.090 align:middle line:84%
to play with us, to be
messages and communications

00:37:59.090 --> 00:38:01.140 align:middle line:90%
and work on our behalf?

00:38:01.140 --> 00:38:02.250 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing.

00:38:02.250 --> 00:38:04.584 align:middle line:84%
When I was in retail-- I
was in retail for 30 years--

00:38:04.584 --> 00:38:07.000 align:middle line:84%
and there was this woman that
would walk through the door.

00:38:07.000 --> 00:38:09.290 align:middle line:84%
She had the most gorgeous
curly hair I'd ever seen.

00:38:09.290 --> 00:38:10.272 align:middle line:90%
The sun would shine.

00:38:10.272 --> 00:38:11.480 align:middle line:90%
It would go right through it.

00:38:11.480 --> 00:38:13.636 align:middle line:84%
The angels would
sing, [SINGING] ahhh.

00:38:13.636 --> 00:38:15.760 align:middle line:84%
And I would just fall in
love with this curly hair.

00:38:15.760 --> 00:38:17.660 align:middle line:84%
And I had very,
very straight hair.

00:38:17.660 --> 00:38:19.780 align:middle line:84%
And there was one day
that she walked in

00:38:19.780 --> 00:38:21.690 align:middle line:90%
and the light hit it just right.

00:38:21.690 --> 00:38:24.310 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I will
to have curly hair.

00:38:24.310 --> 00:38:25.922 align:middle line:84%
The next morning I
woke up with this.

00:38:25.922 --> 00:38:27.130 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Are you kidding me?

00:38:27.130 --> 00:38:29.809 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: What if we can change
everything and we just don't--

00:38:29.809 --> 00:38:31.850 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: The women who
are listening, oh my god.

00:38:31.850 --> 00:38:33.810 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: But that
is what has happened.

00:38:33.810 --> 00:38:35.440 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
want people to get.

00:38:35.440 --> 00:38:36.400 align:middle line:90%
You are masters.

00:38:36.400 --> 00:38:37.980 align:middle line:90%
You are gods walking.

00:38:37.980 --> 00:38:40.730 align:middle line:84%
The sacred texts
all tell you this,

00:38:40.730 --> 00:38:43.490 align:middle line:84%
but we just need to know it and
believe it and allow ourselves

00:38:43.490 --> 00:38:44.480 align:middle line:90%
this playground.

00:38:44.480 --> 00:38:45.950 align:middle line:90%
This is not an earth school.

00:38:45.950 --> 00:38:47.810 align:middle line:84%
It's not obstacles
and challenges.

00:38:47.810 --> 00:38:50.070 align:middle line:90%
It's a playground.

00:38:50.070 --> 00:38:53.110 align:middle line:84%
And we are meant to dive
into the dark night.

00:38:53.110 --> 00:38:55.580 align:middle line:84%
And I wrote a song that's
absolutely beautiful

00:38:55.580 --> 00:38:57.270 align:middle line:84%
that speaks about
that dark night.

00:38:57.270 --> 00:38:58.266 align:middle line:84%
>> LILOU: Are you
going to sing for us?

00:38:58.266 --> 00:38:59.710 align:middle line:84%
>> SINGH: I'd be happy
to if you want me to.

00:38:59.710 --> 00:39:00.680 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yay.

00:39:00.680 --> 00:39:01.410 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: Would you like me to?

00:39:01.410 --> 00:39:02.045 align:middle line:90%
>> LILOU: Yeah.

00:39:02.045 --> 00:39:02.586 align:middle line:90%
>> SINGH: OK.

00:39:02.586 --> 00:39:04.937 align:middle line:90%


00:39:04.937 --> 00:39:06.145 align:middle line:90%
I have to do this a cappella.

00:39:06.145 --> 00:39:07.860 align:middle line:90%
We'll see how this works.

00:39:07.860 --> 00:39:15.580 align:middle line:10%
[SINGING] Contracts come, lives
intertwine, anger, sadness,

00:39:15.580 --> 00:39:18.170 align:middle line:10%
grief, and resentment.

00:39:18.170 --> 00:39:24.270 align:middle line:10%
A soul curriculum we must
all learn in our own time.

00:39:24.270 --> 00:39:30.230 align:middle line:10%
Sing your song out loud
while creating your story.

00:39:30.230 --> 00:39:35.670 align:middle line:10%
A spiritual journey,
a human experience.

00:39:35.670 --> 00:39:45.750 align:middle line:10%
There are no mistakes, no
mistakes in all this glory,

00:39:45.750 --> 00:39:50.070 align:middle line:10%
in all this glory.

00:39:50.070 --> 00:39:55.345 align:middle line:84%
All seems lost when
you look in the mirror.

00:39:55.345 --> 00:39:56.580 align:middle line:90%
Hope is gone.

00:39:56.580 --> 00:40:00.870 align:middle line:84%
Let yourself fall
to hear the call.

00:40:00.870 --> 00:40:06.360 align:middle line:84%
This is the beginning
where we learn to belong.

00:40:06.360 --> 00:40:09.570 align:middle line:90%
A life wrought with separation?

00:40:09.570 --> 00:40:15.930 align:middle line:84%
No, it's preparation,
leading you,

00:40:15.930 --> 00:40:22.160 align:middle line:84%
guiding you to who you
are, to who you really are.

00:40:22.160 --> 00:40:28.410 align:middle line:84%
In a moment you'll awaken
to your soul's true call.

00:40:28.410 --> 00:40:34.066 align:middle line:84%
Dark night of the soul,
it's a place where we grow.

00:40:34.066 --> 00:40:38.710 align:middle line:84%
Dark nights, dark nights,
dark nights to behold.

00:40:38.710 --> 00:40:43.910 align:middle line:84%
It's the soul's
path to the light.

00:40:43.910 --> 00:40:49.555 align:middle line:84%
In the darkest night
find your gold.

00:40:49.555 --> 00:40:52.340 align:middle line:90%


00:40:52.340 --> 00:40:55.470 align:middle line:90%
Find your gold.

00:40:55.470 --> 00:41:03.000 align:middle line:84%
Victim, villain, saint, then
sinner, the pebbles and rocks,

00:41:03.000 --> 00:41:04.810 align:middle line:90%
the boulders do rise.

00:41:04.810 --> 00:41:10.530 align:middle line:84%
In the moment of your surrender,
you shall give in to surprise,

00:41:10.530 --> 00:41:15.770 align:middle line:84%
and then you'll have the
chance to discover the winner.

00:41:15.770 --> 00:41:20.810 align:middle line:84%
A hero's journey,
learn to let go.

00:41:20.810 --> 00:41:26.570 align:middle line:84%
Let it go to find
you are the infinite.

00:41:26.570 --> 00:41:29.770 align:middle line:90%
It's just a show.

00:41:29.770 --> 00:41:32.100 align:middle line:90%
Fall to the ground.

00:41:32.100 --> 00:41:34.330 align:middle line:90%
Cry your tears.

00:41:34.330 --> 00:41:36.350 align:middle line:90%
Say your prayer.

00:41:36.350 --> 00:41:38.890 align:middle line:90%
Dive into your fears.

00:41:38.890 --> 00:41:44.550 align:middle line:84%
It's the road of every human
soul, the path of all time,

00:41:44.550 --> 00:41:50.030 align:middle line:84%
to begin this journey believing
we are deaf, dumb, and blind.

00:41:50.030 --> 00:41:53.582 align:middle line:84%
In the land of
opposites, burning

00:41:53.582 --> 00:41:58.600 align:middle line:84%
as an ember, you will
learn to shine where you'll

00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:04.970 align:middle line:84%
find what is mine is yours,
what is yours is mine.

00:42:04.970 --> 00:42:10.780 align:middle line:84%
Dark night of the soul,
it's a place where we grow.

00:42:10.780 --> 00:42:15.050 align:middle line:84%
Dark nights, dark nights,
dark nights to behold.

00:42:15.050 --> 00:42:20.130 align:middle line:84%
It's the soul's
path to the light.

00:42:20.130 --> 00:42:25.794 align:middle line:84%
In the darkest night,
find your gold.

00:42:25.794 --> 00:42:28.510 align:middle line:90%


00:42:28.510 --> 00:42:31.630 align:middle line:90%
Find your gold.

00:42:31.630 --> 00:42:34.040 align:middle line:90%
Now that was six voice lessons.

00:42:34.040 --> 00:42:35.750 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know how to sing.

00:42:35.750 --> 00:42:37.470 align:middle line:90%
I've lost my voice three times.

00:42:37.470 --> 00:42:40.480 align:middle line:84%
And each time I've lost my
voice, it's gotten stronger.

00:42:40.480 --> 00:42:43.700 align:middle line:84%
And over the course--
I've now done 48 shows,

00:42:43.700 --> 00:42:47.730 align:middle line:84%
and my voice has gotten
stronger and stronger.

00:42:47.730 --> 00:42:51.190 align:middle line:84%
The lesson is here is we
don't have to be perfect.

00:42:51.190 --> 00:42:53.230 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to get
it right, that I've

00:42:53.230 --> 00:42:56.280 align:middle line:84%
gained far more through the
experience of discovering

00:42:56.280 --> 00:42:59.270 align:middle line:84%
my courage, my confidence,
my ability to have gifts

00:42:59.270 --> 00:43:01.150 align:middle line:84%
that I didn't even
know that I had.

00:43:01.150 --> 00:43:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And in doing that,
in being the example

00:43:03.190 --> 00:43:05.240 align:middle line:84%
of that to other
people, there are

00:43:05.240 --> 00:43:07.030 align:middle line:84%
fires inside of
people that are being

00:43:07.030 --> 00:43:09.100 align:middle line:90%
lit up all over this country.

00:43:09.100 --> 00:43:13.130 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're here to
do is just do it for ourselves.

00:43:13.130 --> 00:43:14.880 align:middle line:90%
My nickname is Simi.

00:43:14.880 --> 00:43:16.780 align:middle line:90%
Simi, see-me.

00:43:16.780 --> 00:43:19.470 align:middle line:84%
I had to do this for the little
girl that has hidden away

00:43:19.470 --> 00:43:22.180 align:middle line:90%
for 44 years behind four walls.

00:43:22.180 --> 00:43:25.870 align:middle line:84%
I had to get out on stage
and tour the country for me

00:43:25.870 --> 00:43:28.600 align:middle line:90%
so that I would see me.

00:43:28.600 --> 00:43:31.110 align:middle line:84%
And in doing that,
it is allowing others

00:43:31.110 --> 00:43:33.246 align:middle line:84%
to see that they
can see themselves.

00:43:33.246 --> 00:43:34.870 align:middle line:10%
And that's the truth
of why we're here,

00:43:34.870 --> 00:43:38.260 align:middle line:10%
to discover who we are,
to love ourselves enough,

00:43:38.260 --> 00:43:40.380 align:middle line:10%
and to be willing
to stand in that

00:43:40.380 --> 00:43:43.590 align:middle line:10%
so that that world that
appears so real outside also

00:43:43.590 --> 00:43:45.040 align:middle line:10%
can ripple out and do the same.

00:43:45.040 --> 00:43:47.280 align:middle line:10%
>> LILOU: Mmm.

00:43:47.280 --> 00:43:49.140 align:middle line:10%
[SIGHS] This felt really good.

00:43:49.140 --> 00:43:52.120 align:middle line:10%
Thank you so much, Simran,
